text.tspan: Nepal Re-Insurance Company Limited (Nepal Re.), the successor of insurance Pool that was set up in
2003 with the aim to cover damages caused by the terrorism, was incorporated on 7 November 2014,
under the Companies Act, 2006 of Nepal i accordance to the decision of Council of Ministers (Nepal)
dated 7th August, 2014 to convert the Insurance Pool, Nepal into Reinsurance Company. Nepal Re was
formally inaugurated on 22nd December 2014 by the Honble Finance Minister Dr.Ram Sharan Mahat. It
